<img width="1080" height="1080" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Eve-and-Maximillion-Cooper-EOnline-e1644587310363.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image lazyload" alt="" loading="lazy" />  Rapper Eve has given birth to her first child with husband Maximillion Cooper. The 43-year-old rapper whose full name is Eve Jihan Cooper, made the announcement via her Instagram page  on Thursday morning. Eve revealed that she and her husband have welcomed a bouncing baby boy, disclosing the baby’s name as  Wilde Wolf Fife Alexander Somers Cooper. Eve posted a picture of her newborn with the caption “Our Beautiful boy was born Feb 1st 2022. ‘Wilde Wolf Fife Alexander Somers Cooper [two blue heart emojis] Words can’t describe this feeling.” The rapper made the announcement In November that she would be having her first child with the British businessman. ‘Can you believe it we finally get to tell everyone!!!!!’ Eve wrote in  the announcement post. ‘You all know how long we’ve been waiting for this blessing!!! We get to meet our lil human February 2022.’ After four years of dating, Eve married her husband in 2014. Eve’s son made the addition of Maximillion’s four children: Lotus, 19, Jagger, 17, Cash, 15, and Mini, 13.  